---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout>
  <article class="px-4 sm:px-8 py-12 sm:py-16 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-8">About</h1>

    <div
      class="space-y-5 text-base sm:text-lg leading-relaxed text-base-content/90"
    >
      <p>
        The conversation about who actually carries New Zealand's tax burden
        has been stuck for a generation. This site is an attempt to move it.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight pt-6">
        Why New Zealand is unusual
      </h2>

      <p>
        We have no broad capital gains tax — only the bright-line test on
        property and a few narrow rules. We have no inheritance, estate, or
        gift tax; estate duty was abolished in 1992, gift duty in 2011. The
        result is a tax base that leans heavily on income from work, and very
        lightly on wealth that compounds in the background.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight pt-6">
        Why it's been stuck
      </h2>

      <p>
        Every few years a serious proposal comes along and gets quietly
        buried. Governments of both colours have decided taxing wealth is too
        politically expensive to attempt. Meanwhile a generation of Kiwis is
        leaving for wages that buy a life this country no longer can. Plenty
        of comparable economies tax capital gains, wealth, or inheritance and
        fund decent public services with it. That isn't radical. It's normal.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight pt-6">
        Who's behind this
      </h2>

      <p>
        Started by me, Josh Richards — a Kiwi in my late twenties, not a tax
        expert and not a politician. The argument isn't original; Gary
        Stevenson and the team at Gary's Economics have been making the same
        case in the UK for years. This is the New Zealand version.
      </p>

      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight pt-6">The goal</h2>

      <p>
        Shift the conversation. Policy follows public pressure, and right now
        there isn't enough of either. If you can help — writing, design,
        research, organising, or just sharing — get in touch at <a
          href="mailto:hello@twnw.nz"
          class="link link-primary">hello@twnw.nz</a
        >.
      </p>

      <p class="pt-2 text-base-content/70">— Josh</p>
    </div>
  </article>
</Layout>
